GT Solar Receives $218.9 Million Order for Sapphire Production Furnaces

-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 
2011-04-27T14:31:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/gt-solar-receives-218-9-million-order-for-sapphire-production-furnaces.html
GT Solar International Inc. (SOLR) , a
maker of manufacturing equipment for solar cells and synthetic
sapphires, received a $218.9 million order for sapphire
crystallization furnace from Guizhou Haotian Optoelectronics
Technology Co., according to a statement issued today.  GT Solar has received orders totaling $377.5 million for
its sapphire furnaces since the Merrimack, New Hampshire-based
company began selling them in December. Haotian Optoelectronics,
of Guizhou,  China , is a startup that plans to make sapphires for
light-emitting diodes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in New York at 
 egoossens1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  